EXTRACTED VALUE: FIrst impression: needs updating. The place isn't "trendy old," it's just worn and dated. We figured the ffod would make up for it.
Boy were we right. The portions were tiny- my caesar salad was drenched in dressing and cheap parmesan cheese- I have had better at Macaroni Grill.
The prices have gone up, but there are not very many deals in Midtown that can match the Burger Joint.
However, while all the pastas were very good, the menu was hardly inventive: a short-rib-stuffed pasta w/ tomato sauce? pasta bologenese?
As for the food, it'stough to beat their unusual and imaginative specials.
Definitely a must-visit when you are on-island. No vacation is complete without at least one Rorschach Lobster tee and a Bungaccino.
Over all we were very disappointed with the service, quality and price of our dinner.
This is a restaurant that truly deserves its hype. Also, our waitress was amazing.
